{"version":3,"kind":"Article","sha256":"3459aab2c277ff34bef7e64389abd5dddaf38acc959e7dbb501125780be1f7f2","slug":"papers.rram-devices.index","location":"/papers/rram-devices/index.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"RRAM Devices","description":"Resistive RAM, oxide switching, filament formation, sneak currents, crossbar arrays, and in-memory computing.","content_includes_title":false,"exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"index.md","url":"/index-e5247fdb7a9f7e2e5812f95c0b3233bb.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Scope","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"key":"SOEM9klK7y"}],"identifier":"scope","label":"Scope","html_id":"scope","implicit":true,"key":"RsaK6BgAza"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Resistive RAM (RRAM) stores data as the resistance state of a metal-insulator-metal stack. Switching between high-resistance and low-resistance states proceeds through the formation and rupture of nanoscale conductive filaments: oxygen vacancies or metal cations driven through a thin oxide layer by electric field, Joule heating, and redox reactions. RRAM is among the most mature memristive technologies, with commercial deployment in multiple forms.","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"LlCoThNOZR"}],"key":"R5YBS5kFKv"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Relevance","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"hpHuYasW3m"}],"identifier":"relevance","label":"Relevance","html_id":"relevance","implicit":true,"key":"BVS9j9hynp"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1},"end":{"